Police are looking for a gang that attacked and robbed a motorist on Thika Road as he sought help after his car stalled near Utalii College. The motorist said two men riding on a motorbike stopped on the roadside where his car had stalled and inquired what the problem was. ALSO READ:

'Leader' of dangerous gang appears in court And when he informed them of the incident they turned on him and robbed him of his Sh7,000 and other valuables before riding off to unknown destination. Police say the man reported of the incident long after the riders had escaped and efforts to trace them are ongoing. Such incidents are common on the major roads in the city. Police advise motorists affected in such incidents to seek help from authorities.